Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.72,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.93,0:01:41.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This way! Start chopping\Nthe walls down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.13,0:01:43.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll make our firebreak here\Nto keep the fire from spreading!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.62,0:02:06.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's a ruisha.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.06,0:02:09.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Take good care of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.03,0:02:13.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The person you were as\NPrince Chagum died tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.10,0:02:17.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, you're going\Nto live as just Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.80,0:02:21.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once I accept a job,\NI see it through no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.94,0:02:24.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to let you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.91,0:02:27.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I was hired to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.21,0:02:30.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know it will be difficult for you,\Nbut bear with it and survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.95,0:02:34.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you do, one day you might\Nbe reunited with your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.99,0:02:39.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.86,0:02:50.87,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 2\NHunters, Hunted
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.31,0:03:00.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They haven't managed\Nto put out the fire yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.01,0:03:04.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Gakai...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.35,0:03:11.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the third time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.49,0:03:15.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Three times, the prince's\Nlife has been threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.19,0:03:18.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So they still haven't\Ndetermined if he survived?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.06,0:03:20.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.87,0:03:26.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, Shuga...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.47,0:03:32.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These rumors of Prince Chagum\Nbeing possessed, are they true?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.18,0:03:39.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As tutor-governor\Nof Ichinomiya Palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.02,0:03:43.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I like to think that I know\Neverything about Prince Sagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.79,0:03:47.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, no matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.52,0:03:52.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even assuming that Prince Chagum\Nhas, in fact, perished in this fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.30,0:03:55.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...perhaps it is for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.40,0:03:59.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the unthinkable happened and\Nthese unpleasant rumors had spread...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.60,0:04:03.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it might have greatly hampered\Nthe government's ability to function.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.81,0:04:07.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you will excuse me,\NI will return to my devotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.44,0:04:36.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, I'll carry you piggyback.\NYou're asleep on your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.51,0:04:42.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter? Hop on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.35,0:04:46.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What does this "piggyback" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.99,0:04:53.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Piggyback means being\Ncarried on someone's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:55.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commoner children...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.12,0:04:59.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...are carried on the backs of their\Nmothers from the day they're born.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.96,0:05:06.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no shame in being carried.\NEveryone grows up doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.17,0:05:08.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hop on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.21,0:05:18.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's warmer and more comfortable\Nfor you this way, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.65,0:05:21.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.17,0:05:40.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is Shuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.94,0:05:44.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have come to ask for an audience\Nwith the master star reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.64,0:06:14.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why have you come?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.50,0:06:17.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I already know about Ninomiya Palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.97,0:06:19.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Star Reader...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.68,0:06:24.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Prince Sagum, the heir to the throne,\Nis not in the best of health.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.35,0:06:28.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One would think that Prince Chagum\Nwould be vital to us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:31.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What, exactly, are you implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.83,0:06:39.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The remainder of this conversation\Nwill take place before empty vessels.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.33,0:06:46.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I may...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.14,0:06:52.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe His Majesty ordered\Nthe death of Prince Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:54.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His death?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.08,0:06:57.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I prayed that\NI was worrying needlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.98,0:07:00.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I can no longer fool myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.28,0:07:05.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His Highness began to meet with\Nstrange accidents one after another...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.86,0:07:08.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...immediately after I reported\Nhis condition to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.19,0:07:11.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The prince is\Ndescended from the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.86,0:07:15.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He cannot be possessed by\Nevil spirits under any circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.43,0:07:21.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of whether he was ever,\Nin fact, truly possessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.60,0:07:25.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But was there truly nothing\Nthat could have been done for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.21,0:07:27.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do not speak so glibly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.91,0:07:31.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten the message that\Nthe second queen sent to that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.45,0:07:32.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...common magic weaver?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.05,0:07:36.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is due to your hasty, reckless\Nactions as his tutor-governor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.66,0:07:42.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, unlike the earlier\Nincidents, the fire tonight...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.69,0:07:45.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...was not set on\Nthe orders of His Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.07,0:07:50.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.83,0:07:54.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...if you focus too long on\Nthe workings of politics and the stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:07:59.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...you will soon lose sight of\Nthe workings of the human heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.91,0:08:05.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had forgotten that\Nthe second queen is also a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.35,0:08:09.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am told that she summoned\Nto Ninomiya Palace last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.52,0:08:12.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...a female bodyguard who\Nhad saved the life of the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.39,0:08:15.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Deducing that\Nher son was in danger...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.42,0:08:20.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...she likely used this bodyguard\Nto allow the prince to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.86,0:08:23.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The fire is merely a ploy\Nto cover their tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.23,0:08:25.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt that you will find his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.77,0:08:27.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then Prince Chagum is still...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.14,0:08:32.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you are to speak of this to no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.41,0:08:36.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A significant number have heard\Nthis rumor of a possessing spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.48,0:08:39.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Prince Chagum is believed\Nto have died in the fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.88,0:08:42.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it will be convenient\Nfor all concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.06,0:08:49.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, how do you believe\Nthe prince managed to escape...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.96,0:08:53.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...all of those drowning\Nattempts so easily?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.33,0:08:59.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In my humble opinion, I believe that\Nthe evil spirit possessing him...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.54,0:09:02.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is in all likelihood a water demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.97,0:09:06.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By "water demon," do you\Nmean that water demon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.34,0:09:07.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.91,0:09:11.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The water demon depicted in\NThe Official History of Shin- Yogo...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.11,0:09:14.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the chronicle of\NShin-Yogo's creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.35,0:09:16.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.75,0:09:23.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have always greatly\Nvalued your ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.59,0:09:26.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For that reason,\NI feel that I must warn you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.13,0:09:29.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should you go on involving yourself\Nin the government's dark side...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.90,0:09:34.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...you will be going down\Na path of no return.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.87,0:09:37.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A dark, sinister underbelly\Nto the star palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.54,0:09:41.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...whose existence you\Nmost likely never suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.81,0:09:46.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have always been taught\Nthat the world is composed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.92,0:09:49.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...of light and darkness\Nin equal measure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.25,0:09:55.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how dark and twisted\Nthe path may be, if it leads to heaven...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.29,0:09:57.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...then I should like to walk down it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.46,0:09:59.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.23,0:10:06.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let that be the one and only\Nlight to illuminate your path.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.94,0:10:08.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.94,0:10:15.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With His Majesty's consent,\NI have decided to dispatch pursuers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.14,0:10:17.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To bring back the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.18,0:10:19.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To what end?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.18,0:10:24.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Going back to my question earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.75,0:10:30.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it is most likely a water demon\Nthat has possessed the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.43,0:10:36.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is why I intended to use fire\Nto try to kill it in our third attempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.44,0:10:46.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Official History tells us that at\Na spring fed by the Aoyumi River...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.58,0:10:50.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Torugaru, the first mikado of\Nthe Shin-Yogo empire...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.51,0:10:56.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...slew a water demon that\Nhad possessed a Yakoo child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.62,0:10:59.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Upon doing this,\Nhe declared himself mikado...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.46,0:11:02.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the son of heaven, one who\Nreceives the blessings of the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.63,0:11:04.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The child was possessed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.33,0:11:10.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From this, we can deduce it is\Nimpossible for anyone other than one...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.07,0:11:14.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who has received heaven's blessings\Nto take a water demon's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.44,0:11:16.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.14,0:11:21.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Upon Prince Chagum's return...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.01,0:11:25.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the mikado himself will\Nslay it using Star's Heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.28,0:11:28.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the blade passed down\Nfrom Torugaru's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.98,0:11:30.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But he cannot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.05,0:11:31.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely that would be much too...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.15,0:11:32.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely that would be much too...\NYou need not tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.16,0:11:37.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Behind the bamboo blinds,\NHis Majesty was weeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.99,0:11:41.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it is for the\Ngood of the government...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.06,0:11:47.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...he must take the life of his own son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.00,0:11:53.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am sure that you understand how\Ngreat the mikado's suffering must be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.05,0:12:03.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These are the Hunters,\Nwho serve the mikado in secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.69,0:12:08.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Their true identity is known\Nonly by the mikado and myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.66,0:12:14.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now, you will be the third to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.00,0:12:22.00,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.88,0:13:08.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Toya?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.92,0:13:10.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Toya, are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.09,0:13:14.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.42,0:13:16.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.04,0:13:30.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.51,0:13:34.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you're back in town?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.74,0:13:36.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time, Toya.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.45,0:13:38.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Saya, I didn't mean\Nto wake you up too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.55,0:13:41.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's all right.\NI was about to get up anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.72,0:13:42.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.92,0:13:47.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, do you two\Nknow where Torogai is now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.86,0:13:52.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I haven't heard anything\Nabout her in town lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:53.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.13,0:13:54.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind then. Forget I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.23,0:13:56.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up, Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.20,0:13:58.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you haven't run into Tanda yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.03,0:14:01.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's here in town?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.27,0:14:05.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He said he thought you would\Nbe coming back any day now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.91,0:14:08.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.38,0:14:09.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.12,0:14:16.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do, kidnap\Nsome nobleman's child?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.42,0:14:17.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hardly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.36,0:14:22.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been hired as\Nthis boy's bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.69,0:14:25.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please, have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.90,0:14:28.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.37,0:14:30.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.67,0:14:34.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go into details with you, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.37,0:14:36.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.18,0:14:45.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Toya, will you use this money\Nto buy a few things for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.81,0:14:52.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just name it. I'd do anything for you,\Ncome hell or high water.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.02,0:14:54.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.76,0:14:59.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, I need ten big sheets\Nof oiled paper to keep the rain out...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.96,0:15:03.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and a bear pelt warm enough\Nfor sleeping on a snowy mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.50,0:15:06.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I also need ten days' worth\Nof dried meat and rice cakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.67,0:15:08.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also a set of clothes\Nthat will fit the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.64,0:15:12.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave it to me.\NIs there anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.34,0:15:14.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One last thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.71,0:15:17.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A horse that can\Nhandle a long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.91,0:15:19.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A horse?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.78,0:15:21.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is a 10,000 Iugal gold coin!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.08,0:15:25.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will buying a horse on the spot,\Neven for 10,000 lugals, be trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.89,0:15:27.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think you're talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.66,0:15:32.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Around here, I'm the most reliable\Nerrand runner there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.30,0:15:42.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do your legs hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.91,0:15:53.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here, rub this on the parts that hurt.\NIt'll make them feel a little better.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.42,0:15:55.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do it yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.82,0:15:57.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.69,0:16:01.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That comes to twenty Iugal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.22,0:16:04.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty? Oh, come on now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.49,0:16:07.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How about this much?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.06,0:16:10.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ten? Are you trying\Nto drive me out of business?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.27,0:16:13.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what're you talking about?\NIt's spring already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.84,0:16:17.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't sell this bear pelt now,\Nit'll just sit here till winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.41,0:16:20.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sixteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.38,0:16:23.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're a sensible man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.85,0:16:25.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.21,0:16:28.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Until those two get back, stay in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.46,0:16:43.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Keep the straw mat pulled over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.03,0:16:46.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's far better than catching a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.31,0:16:56.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ordinary people certainly wouldn't\Nbe walking around with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.19,0:17:12.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the time comes,\NI'll use these, Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.00,0:17:23.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see that\Ncommotion last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.34,0:17:27.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, judging from the direction,\Nit was at Ninomiya Palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.41,0:17:30.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have to say it'll be\Nsomething else if somebody died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:32.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know, a certain\Nsomeone who lives there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.71,0:17:35.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! Don't even joke about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.36,0:17:45.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to regret not having gone\Nstraight to the blacksmith's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.33,0:18:18.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.00,0:18:27.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in over my head here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.84,0:18:30.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But without Torogai's help, I cannot...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.11,0:18:32.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.14,0:18:34.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.08,0:18:38.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.05,0:18:41.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I must have been acting\Nstrangely once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.42,0:18:44.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Were you having\Na nightmare or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.59,0:18:46.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do not remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.66,0:18:52.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But whenever this happens,\NI feel an overwhelming urge to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.06,0:18:58.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you? I won't\Nlet you die, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.53,0:18:59.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.90,0:19:04.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the first time\NI've experienced this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.21,0:19:06.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I've been\Npossessed by whatever this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.41,0:19:09.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I've felt a desire to survive,\Nand I don't know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.35,0:19:21.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're throwing quite a lot\Nof money around, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.89,0:19:24.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now a horse too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.53,0:19:28.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you planning to cross the\NMisty Blue Mountains or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.90,0:19:31.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How is that any of your business?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.57,0:19:36.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to buy it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.34,0:19:39.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As they say, "A weak seam\Nin one's travelling clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.71,0:19:42.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...will grow into a hole\Nwhile on the road."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.01,0:19:43.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody asked you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.15,0:19:52.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good, this will be plenty for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.02,0:19:55.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad. Also, take these.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.73,0:20:00.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The shop where I bought these\Nmakes delicious lunches.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.60,0:20:03.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You two are really thoughtful!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.33,0:20:07.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Eat while we have the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.51,0:20:15.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I got everything else,\Nbut I'm still working on the horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.55,0:20:21.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, are you planning to\Ncross the Misty Blue Mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.12,0:20:22.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What makes you ask that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.15,0:20:27.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, some strange guy asked me\Nthat while I was out shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.26,0:20:31.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But no need to worry.\NI managed to deflect his questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.76,0:20:35.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You think fast on your feet.\NDon't worry about the horse any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.73,0:20:38.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to have to set out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.47,0:20:43.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but you two need to\Npack up your things right away too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.41,0:20:44.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.57,0:20:48.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If they find out about this place,\Nit'll mean trouble for you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.69,0:20:59.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is to thank you\Nfor all you've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.86,0:21:02.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't take this much!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.26,0:21:03.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.53,0:21:07.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you to leave your home.\NThis is nowhere near enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.10,0:21:11.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? But I was the one who\Ncouldn't come through for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.93,0:21:15.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you mustn't use\Nthe coins until next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.54,0:21:16.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.94,0:21:19.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.47,0:21:21.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye! Take care of yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.07,0:21:46.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are your legs bothering you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.24,0:21:51.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.98,0:21:54.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.91,0:21:59.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't a prince\Nfor nothing, were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.05,0:22:01.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have grit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.79,0:22:08.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not having a horse is going\Nto make this a lot tougher...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.34,0:22:28.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A double moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.64,0:22:30.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.95,0:22:34.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good. There's nowhere\Nfor us to hide out here, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.23,0:22:49.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum! Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.87,0:22:56.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Run, I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:45.28,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.54,0:24:45.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa battles the Hunters alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.55,0:24:48.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, she is mortally\Nwounded by an enemy blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.68,0:24:51.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Fight to the Death."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:53.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What does Balsa see...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 3\NFight to the Death

Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.59,0:24:55.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...as her consciousness slips away?
